{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"410ccc–23","heading":"Preparation of plan","label":"410ccc–23 Preparation of plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch1/schLIX–AA/ptB","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an inventory of important properties and cultural landscapes that should be preserved, managed, developed, and maintained because of their cultural, natural, and public use significance;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an analysis of current land uses within the area and how they affect the goals of preservation and public use of the heritage area;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an interpretive plan to address the cultural and natural history of the area, and actions to enhance visitor use. This element of the plan shall be undertaken in consultation with the National Park Service and visitor use plans for the historical park;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recommendations for coordinating actions by local, State, and Federal governments within the heritage area, to further the purposes of this subchapter; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an implementation program for the plan including desired actions by State and local governments and other involved groups and entities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Approval of plan","label":"b Approval of plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"whether the Commission has afforded adequate opportunity, including public meetings and hearings, for public and governmental involvement in the preparation of the plan; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"whether reasonable assurances have been received from the State and local governments that the plan is supported and that the implementation program is feasible.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Disapproval of plan","label":"c Disapproval of plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410ccc–23","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410ccc%E2%80%9323%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If the Secretary disapproves the plan, he shall advise the Commission in writing of the reasons for disapproval, and shall provide recommendations and assistance in the revision plan. Following completion of any revisions to the plan, the Commission shall resubmit the plan to the Governor of Louisiana for approval, and to the Secretary, who shall approve or disapprove the plan within 90 days after the date that the plan is revised.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
